M||tx|---
M||name|finances
M||desc|"Use this skill when the us needs to bd a financial md, calculate unit economics, understand MRR/ARR/churn, or figure out their quit number. Covers SaaS metrics, CAC/LTV, burn rate, cash flow modeling, and making unit economics legible for non-fi founders."
M||tx|---
M|SaaS|tx|A SaaS business is a math machine. If you don't know your numbers, you're guessing. This skill makes unit economics legible — MRR, CAC, LTV, churn, burn rate — clear enough to make decisions, rigorous enough to be trusted.
M|Core|it|A SaaS business is a math machine. If you don't know your numbers, you're guessing.
M|Core|it|Unit economics tell the truth abt your business long before your bank account does.
M|Core|it|The only financial md that matters for a solo founder is one that fits on a single spreadsheet and gets updated monthly.
M|Core|it|rv is vanity. Margin is sanity. Cash flow is reality.
M|Core|- Ev|"shd I spend more here?" or "Is this working?"
