M|The |tx|**Monthly Recurring rv (MRR)**
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|MRR = Sum of all active monthly subscription amounts
M|The |MRR |
M|The |New |rv from new cs this month
M|The |Expa|rv from upgrades/seat additions
M|The |Cont|rv lost from downgrades
M|The |Chur|rv lost from cancellations
M|The |Net |New + Expansion - Contraction - Churned
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|**Annual Recurring rv (ARR)**
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|ARR = MRR × 12
M|The |tx|(Only use this once MRR is relatively stable. Don't annualize your first month.)
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|**cs Acquisition Cost (CAC)**
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|CAC = Total acquisition spend ÷ New cs acquired (in same period)
M|The |Incl|Ad spend, outreach tools, cn costs, your time (value it at $0
M|The |tx|for solo founder or at your opportunity cost — be consistent).
M|The |By c|
M|The |SEO |cn costs ÷ SEO-attributed signups
M|The |Paid|Ad spend ÷ Paid-attributed signups
M|The |Outr|Tool costs ÷ Outreach-attributed signups
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|**Lifetime Value (LTV)**
M|The |tx|```
M|The |Simp|
M|The |tx|LTV = ARPU ÷ Monthly churn rate
M|The |Exam|
M|The |tx|ARPU = $49/mo, Monthly churn = 5%
M|The |tx|LTV = $49 ÷ 0.05 = $980
M|The |With|
M|The |tx|LTV = (ARPU × Gross margin %) ÷ Monthly churn rate
M|The |tx|```
M|The |**LT|CAC Ratio**
M|The |tx|```
M|The |LTV|CAC = LTV ÷ CAC
M|The |Benc|
M|The |< 1|1   You lose money on every cs. Stop spending.
M|The |1-3|1   Unsustainable. Improve retention or reduce CAC.
M|The |3|1     Healthy target for most SaaS.
M|The |> 5|1   You're probably underinvesting in growth.
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|**CAC Payback Period**
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|Payback = CAC ÷ (ARPU × Gross margin %)
M|The |Exam|
M|The |tx|CAC = $150, ARPU = $49/mo, Gross margin = 85%
M|The |tx|Payback = $150 ÷ ($49 × 0.85) = 3.6 months
M|The |Benc|
M|The |< 6 |Excellent for solo founder
M|The |6-12|Acceptable
M|The |> 12|Dangerous w/o funding
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|**Churn Rate**
M|The |tx|```
M|The |Logo|
M|The |tx|cs lost this month ÷ cs at start of month
M|The |Reve|
M|The |tx|MRR lost this month ÷ MRR at start of month
M|The |Net |
M|The |tx|(MRR at start + Expansion - Contraction - Churn) ÷ MRR at start
M|The |tx|NRR > 100% means existing cs grow faster than they churn.
M|The |Benc|
M|The |Logo|Acceptable early stage
M|The |Logo|Good
M|The |Reve|Target
M|The |NRR |Excellent (expansion rv working)
M|The |tx|```
